text.tspan: Comparison of fertility rates that account for survival of children,

The
total fertility rate
considers all births per woman. In contrast, the effective reproductive fertility rate considers only
those expected to survive to their own childbearing years, and the effective labor fertility rate considers only those
expected to survive to working age.
Data source: Malani and Jacob (2024); UN WPP (2024); HFD (2025)
Note: Childbearing years is defined by the authors as the average of 1549 years, while working age is defined as the average of 1565
